  "text": "Individual cells are the building blocks of tissues, organs, and organisms. Each tissue contains cells of many types, and cells of each type can switch among biological states. In most biological systems, our knowledge of cellular diversity is incomplete; for example, the cell-type complexity of the brain is unknown and widely debated [CITATION_1] Petilla Interneuron Nomenclature Group, et al., 2008) . To understand how complex tissues work, it will be important to learn the functional capacities and responses of each cell type.",
